            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The second case is interpreted as: `autocmd VimResized * :wincmd = | set number`, which is an `autocmd` that executes both `wincmd =` and `set number` on `VimResized`. You can confirm this by running `autocmd VimResized` and noting the output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n:autocmd VimResized\r\n--- Autocommands ---\r\nVimResized\r\n    *         :wincmd =^@set number^@\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis happens because `$VIMINIT` is meant to set a single command line. If you resize Neovim, the autocmd will fire, and you'll notice the number line will turn on.",
