            "body": "That's interesting! However when I use an multi-line example without a `*` it does seem to work:\r\n\r\n```\r\nset number\r\nset hlsearch\r\nset incsearch\r\nset lazyredraw \r\nset ruler\r\nset autowrite\r\nset autoread\r\nset spelllang=en\r\nnoremap <silent> k gk\r\nnoremap <silent> j gj\r\nset spellsuggest=8\r\nnoremap <silent> 0 g0\r\nnoremap <silent> $ g$\r\nonoremap <silent> j gj\r\nonoremap <silent> k gk\r\n```\r\nAnd is there something like `;` to denote end of command in vimscript?",
